      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 2004 Porsche 911 (996) Turbo equipped with the coveted X50 Performance Package. This example features the legendary 3.6L Mezger flat-six, utilizing a true dry-sump lubrication system and derived from the GT1 Le Mans program. The X50 factory upgrade includes larger K24 turbochargers, revised intercoolers, and a reinforced Getrag G96/50 six-speed manual transaxle, delivering a linear 444 hp to the sophisticated all-wheel-drive system. The chassis remains taut with zero bushing deflection, and the hydraulic steering rack provides surgical feedback. Finished in concours-level paint with a flawless underbody, this Turbo retains its original factory cross-drilled rotors and multi-piston Monobloc calipers. No IMS bearing concerns here\u2014just pure, bulletproof engineering. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, this is a turnkey specimen for the discerning collector seeking peak analog performance.",
